Saving Excell Spreadsheets
--------------------------

after saving .xlsx to .csv on mac, end of line is '^M'.  need to filter 
into unix end-of-line:

tr '\r' '\n' < input_data.csv > converted

Turns out not to be needed.  cvs.reader defaults to EOL chars of either '\r' or '\n'.





Excell tips
-----------

making a column post dollars:
select column
under 'number' dropdown select 'Accounting'

making a column sortable:
click on 'filter' icon


summing by category:
filter by property
select amount category columns
copy to new table (sheet)
go to the pivot table sheet
select 'sum of amount' table (exclude income, net income)
click on table
click on 'pivottable' menu on top bar
select 'change source'
click icon to right of location field
go to filtered table, select amount, category columns




